New York Times Best sellers - Fiction

The New York Times best selling Fiction print/eBook of October 20, 2013

This weeks New editions (1, 4, 7, 10, 11, 13, 20, 22, 24, 25, +Bonus)

1 - GONE - James Patterson and Michael Ledwidge
Detective Michael Bennett, living with his 10 adopted children on a California farm, is pursued by the head of a Mexican drug cartel he once put in jail.
2- DOCTOR SLEEP - Stephen King
Now grown up, Dan, the boy with psycho-intuitive powers in  The Shining,  helps another child with a spectacular gift.
Bonus: Book 1 - The Shining
3 - THE LONGEST RIDE - Nicholas Sparks
The lives of two couples converge unexpectedly.
4 - SILENCING EVE - Iris Johansen
The final book of a trilogy about the forensic sculptor Eve Duncan.
See August 4, 2013 Collection for Books 1 & 2
5- THE HUSBAND'S SECRET - Liane Moriarty
A woman reads a letter from her husband, very much alive, that was intended to be opened only after his death.
6 - NEVER GO BACK - Lee Child
Jack Reacher is thrown into jail on trumped-up charges and must clear his name.
7 - THE SIGNATURE OF ALL THINGS - Elizabeth Gilbert
A 19th-century botanist s love of knowledge takes her to Tahiti; by the author of  Eat, Pray, Love.  
8 - THE RACKETEER - John Grisham
An imprisoned ex-lawyer schemes to exchange information about who murdered a judge for his freedom.
9 - W IS FOR WASTED - Sue Grafton
A homeless man inexplicably leaves $600,000 to Kinsey Millhone.
10 - THE OCTOBER LIST - Jeffery Deaver
A woman innocently finds herself in possession of a list that makes her the target of ruthless criminals. (Novel is told in reverse order)
11 - THE TRAINING - Tara Sue Me
In the conclusion to the Submissive trilogy, Abby King's relationship with Nathaniel West, the millionaire C.E.O. and New York's most eligible dominant, becomes more intimate.
Bonus Books: 1 - The Submissive & 2 - The Dominant
12 - ENDER'S GAME - Orson Scott Card
Government agencies breed child geniuses and train them as soldiers.
13 - POSSESSION - J.R. Ward
Book 5 of the Fallen Angels paranormal romance series.
14 - THE LOWLAND - Jhumpa Lahiri
After his radical brother is killed, an Indian scientist brings his widow to join him in America.
15 - THE QUEST - Nelson DeMille
An elderly priest, recently escaped from an Ethiopian jail, is joined by two journalists in a search for a holy relic.
16 - DEADLINE - Sandra Brown
A journalist becomes a murder suspect as he pursues a story.
17 - THE CUCKOO'S CALLING - Robert Galbraith
The struggling detective Cormoran Strike investigates a supermodel s suicide; by J.K. Rowling, writing pseudonymously.
18 - THANKLESS IN DEATH - J. D. Robb
Lt. Eve Dallas searches for a young man who murdered his parents; by Nora Roberts, writing pseudonymously.
19 - THE FINAL CUT - Catherine Coulter and J.?T. Ellison
A Scotland Yard chief inspector teams up with two special agents from the F.B.I. to hunt for an international jewel thief.
20- WELCOME TO THE WORLD, BABY GIRL! - Fannie Flagg
The pleasures and problems of the rising star of a 1970s television show. Originally published in 1998.
21 - INFERNO - Dan Brown
The symbologist Robert Langdon, on the run in Florence, must decipher a series of codes created by a Dante-loving scientist.
22 - TORN - Kim Karr
Someone from Dahlia London's past resurfaces, and her rock star boyfriend River Wilde's secrets come to light. Can their relationship withstand this turmoil? Book 2 of the Connections series.
Bonus: Book 1 - Connected
23 - GONE GIRL - Gillian Flynn
A woman disappears on the day of her fifth anniversary; is her husband a killer?
24 - CARVED IN BONE - Jefferson Bass
When the forensic anthropologist Bill Brockton is called to examine a mummified corpse discovered in an isolated community, long-hidden secrets and feuds come to light. Originally published in 2006.
25 - THE WAGER - Rachel Van Dyken
The Seattle millionaire Jake Titus begins to fall for the TV reporter Char Lynn, whom he once dropped after a one-night stand. Can he convince her that he's serious this time? Book 2 of The Bet series.

Bonus title from Hardcover list
- BASTION - Mercedes Lackey
Mags and his friends leave Collegium - the heart of Valdemar - for Bastion, the hidden spot in the hills that had once been the headquarters of a powerful band of raiders that had held him and his parents prisoner. Fifth book in the Valdemar: Collegium Chronicles series.
Bonus Books 1-4 of the Collegium Chronicles (Foundation, Intrigues, Changes, Redoubt)
